  "prompt": "How does modern day SEO work on a website?",
  "response": "Modern SEO (Search Engine Optimization) involves several key strategies:\n\n1. On-Page SEO\n- Keyword optimization in content\n- Quality, relevant content creation\n- Proper HTML heading structure\n- Meta descriptions and title tags\n- Internal linking\n- Mobile responsiveness\n- Page load speed optimization\n\n2. Technical SEO\n- XML sitemap creation\n- Secure HTTPS connection\n- Clean website architecture\n- Schema markup\n- Crawlability and indexing optimization\n- Structured data implementation\n\n3. Content Strategy\n- Long-form, in-depth content\n- Regular content updates\n- Solving user search intent\n- Multimedia content\n- Evergreen content creation\n\n4. Off-Page SEO\n- Quality backlink building\n- Social media signals\n- Online reputation management\n- Guest posting\n- Influencer collaborations\n\n5. User Experience\n- Low bounce rates\n- High engagement metrics\n- Easy navigation\n- Fast loading times\n- Mobile-friendly design\n\n6. Advanced Techniques\n- Voice search optimization\n- AI-driven content strategies\n- Featured snippet targeting\n- Local SEO optimization\n- Video and image SEO\n\n7. Analytics and Monitoring\n- Google Analytics tracking\n- Search console monitoring\n- Performance measurement\n- Continuous improvement\n\nThese strategies help websites rank higher in search engine results pages (SERPs).",
